<%= render(DemoComponent.new(
      title: "Snake",
      summary: "Snakes need to eat, too!",
      demo: "/snakes/demo",
      gists: [
        "app/javascript/stylesheets/snake.scss",
        "app/views/snakes/_demo.html.erb",
        "app/javascript/controllers/snake_controller.js",
        "app/controllers/snakes_controller.rb",
        "app/reflexes/snake_reflex.rb"
      ]
    )) do |component| %>
  <% component.with(:explanation) do %>
    <p>
      However impractical it might seem, we wanted to demonstrate that StimulusReflex can
      emit updates fast enough to manage 60fps on a local connection. While you probably
      shouldn't port Doom, please consider yourself dared.
    </p>
    <p>
      At this time, this is a <strong>desktop-only</strong> demo as it relies on the arrow keys to steer.
    </p>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
